<HEAD>Gumbel And Letterman Reportedly Talking Again</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 Fresh from his `` kiss and make-up'' session with `` Today'' show weatherman <PERSON> Willard </PERSON> <PERSON> Scott </PERSON>, <PERSON> Bryant </PERSON> <PERSON> Gumbel </PERSON> has apparently wiped another entry off his grudge slate _ <PERSON> David </PERSON> <PERSON> Letterman </PERSON>. <PERSON> Gumbel </PERSON> called the host of `` Late Night with <PERSON> David </PERSON> <PERSON> Letterman </PERSON>'' recently to thank him for returning a copy of the now-famous memo <PERSON> Gumbel </PERSON> had written criticizing some `` Today'' co-workers, including <PERSON> Scott </PERSON>, the <ORGANIZATION> Daily </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> News </ORGANIZATION> reported today. The newspaper said that whoever leaked the memo to the news media apparently also sent a copy to <PERSON> Letterman </PERSON>, with whom <PERSON> Gumbel </PERSON> had been feuding. That rift began when <PERSON> Letterman </PERSON> used a bullhorn to interrupt a taping of the `` Today'' show in 1985 at the Rockefeller Center skating rink. <PERSON> Letterman </PERSON> had shouted down from a building overlooking the rink, `` I am <PERSON> Larry </PERSON> <PERSON> Grossman </PERSON>, president of <ORGANIZATION> NBC </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> News </ORGANIZATION> ... and I'm not wearing any pants! <PERSON> Gumbel </PERSON> was reportedly furious, but according to <PERSON> Letterman </PERSON>'s executive producer, <PERSON> Jack </PERSON> <PERSON> Rollins </PERSON>, `` the two of them are back talking. Asked if <PERSON> Gumbel </PERSON> might agree to appear again on <PERSON> Letterman </PERSON>'s show, also on <ORGANIZATION> NBC </ORGANIZATION>, <PERSON> Rollins </PERSON> said, `` Anything can happen, but that's not up to me.'' On Monday, <PERSON> Scott </PERSON> kissed <PERSON> Gumbel </PERSON> on the cheek during the `` Today'' show as they buried their hatchet.
