Hastings </PERSON> was in <LOCATION> Washington </LOCATION> for a testimonial dinner for Borders the day the <ORGANIZATION> FBI </ORGANIZATION> sprang its trap. Informed that agents wanted to question him, he left his suite in the plush L'Enfant Plaza Hotel without packing or checking out and told a friend he was taking a cab to <LOCATION> National </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Airport </LOCATION>, four miles away. Instead, he traveled more than 30 miles to <LOCATION> Baltimore-Washington </LOCATION> <LOCATION> International </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Airport </LOCATION> and caught a flight to <LOCATION> Miami </LOCATION> but deplaned in <LOCATION> Fort </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Lauderdale </LOCATION> and rented a car to drive to <LOCATION> Miami </LOCATION>. His own auto at the time was parked at the <LOCATION> Miami </LOCATION> airport.
