<HEAD>Three Magistrates Arrested, 2 Policemen Suspended in Torture Probe</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By ELIZABETH LOVE</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>Associated Press Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>ASUNCION, Paraguay (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 Authorities arrested three town magistrates and suspended two <LOCATION> Asuncion </LOCATION> police officers accused of torturing prisoners during the dictatorship of Gen. <PERSON> Alfredo </PERSON> <PERSON> Stroessner </PERSON>, officials said Thursday. The arrests and suspensions are part of a campaign launched by Gen. <PERSON> Andres </PERSON> <PERSON> Rodriguez </PERSON>, who toppled <PERSON> Stroessner </PERSON> in a Feb. 3 coup. The magistrates, who have executive and judicial powers akin to those of a mayor or justice of the peace, were accused in the 1979 deaths of 24-year-old <PERSON> Adolfo </PERSON> <PERSON> Irala </PERSON> and his brothers, <PERSON> Victor </PERSON>, 19, and <PERSON> Sindulfo </PERSON>, 27. They died in <LOCATION> Tebicuarymi </LOCATION>, a town 80 miles southeast of <LOCATION> Asuncion </LOCATION>. The mother of the three, <PERSON> Leonora </PERSON> <PERSON> Irala </PERSON>, told human rights lawyers her sons were tortured by electric shock and had their teeth pulled out with pliers. `` My sons' cries and screams for help could be heard in the whole town,'' Mrs. <PERSON> Irala </PERSON> was quoted as telling the <LOCATION> Asuncion </LOCATION> newspaper <ORGANIZATION> El </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Diario </ORGANIZATION>. She said her sons were detained and tortured for five days in connection with the slaying of the son of the local ward president of the ruling <ORGANIZATION> Colorado </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Party </ORGANIZATION>. Formal charges have not been filed against <PERSON> Tebicuarymi </PERSON> magistrates <PERSON> Elvio </PERSON> <PERSON> Reyes </PERSON>, <PERSON> Ruben </PERSON> <PERSON> Fernandez </PERSON> and <PERSON> Salustiano </PERSON> <PERSON> Gimenez </PERSON>, authorities said. Police announced the suspension of <LOCATION> Asuncion </LOCATION> officers <PERSON> Augusto </PERSON> <PERSON> Caceres </PERSON> <PERSON> Spelt </PERSON> and <PERSON> Camilo </PERSON> <PERSON> Almada </PERSON> <PERSON> Saprissa </