<HEAD>Eds: SUBS lead and 9th graf pvs, `The defendants ...' to ADD details
of jail's closing and CLARIFY that the city hasn't decided what to do with
the jail.</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By TODD RICHISSIN</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>Associated Press Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>JERSEY CITY, N.J. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 The county jail boiled with rage after a deputy warden and two guards were charged with beating to death an inmate, and the men were held today in a closed municipal jail for their safety. Inmates of the <LOCATION> Hudson </LOCATION> <LOCATION> County </LOCATION> Jail shouted from their cells and smashed windows, and one set a bedsheet on fire outside a window as about 75 relatives and friends of the victim, <PERSON> Arnaldo </PERSON> <PERSON> Ortega </PERSON>, rallied outside on Wednesday. Bedsheets and toilet paper flapped from the windows of some cells. `` People are out here to pay their respects,'' said <PERSON> John </PERSON> <PERSON> Jones </PERSON>, 25, a protester. `` And we're here for justice. Everybody makes mistakes, but they made a big one. That boy had a family and now he's in his grave.'' At least six police officers stood guard outside the jail during the demonstration, and about 20 others watched the crowd. There were no confrontations. Earlier in the day, corrections Officers <PERSON> Thomas </PERSON> <PERSON> Murphy </PERSON>, 39, and <PERSON> David </PERSON> <PERSON> Michael </PERSON> <PERSON> Dumers </PERSON>, 35, and Deputy Warden <PERSON> Raymond </PERSON> <PERSON> Murray </PERSON>, 52, were charged with murdering <PERSON> Ortega </PERSON>, who was in jail on a burglary charge. <LOCATION> Hudson </LOCATION> <LOCATION> County </LOCATION> Prosecutor <PERSON> Paul </PERSON> <PERSON> M. </PERSON> <PERSON> DePascale </PERSON> said <PERSON> Ortega </PERSON>, 28, was beaten for 15 to 20 minutes in a jail elevator and left for 16 hours in a basement holding cell before guards summoned medical help. He died Saturday at a hospital where he was brought two days earlier in a coma. A coroner's report said he was beaten in the head, arms and body. <PERSON> Ortega </PERSON>'s brother, <PERSON> Angel </PERSON>, said inmates told his family that guards used nightsticks on <PERSON> Ortega </PERSON>. The defendants were unable to raise $ 50,000 bail and were sent to the <LOCATION> Bayonne </LOCATION> <LOCATION> City </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Jail </LOCATION>, which was ordered closed by the state a month ago because it had no cameras to watch for suicide attempts. Officials are deciding whether to install cameras. Superior Court Judge <PERSON> Kevin </PERSON> <PERSON> Callahan </PERSON> said he would not send the three to the <LOCATION> Hudson </LOCATION> <LOCATION> County </LOCATION> Jail for fear of exposing them to attacks from other inmates. The county board of freeholders, in response to protests over the killing, said it would investigate allegations about the existence of a `` goon squad'' of corrections workers who routinely beat inmates. <PERSON> DePascale </PERSON> said there is a special unit that responds to crises but that there was no evidence of unprovoked attacks. No other criminal charges are planned, he said.
