<HEAD>Policeman Cleared of Raping Child Is Charged Again</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LYNN, Mass. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 A police officer who was acquitted last summer of sexually abusing a 6-year-old girl was charged Thursday with raping the same child, after police allegedly found a tape of the crime in his apartment. Patrolman <PERSON> Warren </PERSON> <PERSON> A. </PERSON> <PERSON> Poole </PERSON>, 45, was acquitted in June when the girl, placed on the witness stand in front of the defendant, recanted her story of abuse. Several months later, however, the girl told police that <PERSON> Poole </PERSON> had molested her again. After obtaining a search warrant, police raided <PERSON> Poole </PERSON>'s apartment Wednesday and confiscated a videotape that prosecutors said shows the policeman having sex with the girl. <PERSON> Poole </PERSON>, who was suspended without pay after the raid, pleaded innocent at arraignment in <ORGANIZATION> Lynn </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> District </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Court </ORGANIZATION>. Judge <PERSON> Joseph </PERSON> <PERSON> Dever </PERSON> set bail at $ 350,000 with double surety, meaning <PERSON> Poole </PERSON> must put up bonds worth at least $ 700,000 to secure his release. <PERSON> Poole </PERSON>'s attorney, <PERSON> Alan </PERSON> <PERSON> Karahalis </PERSON>, did not respond to telephone messages requesting comment. <PERSON> Poole </PERSON>, a divorced father of six children, has served for 14 years on the police force in <LOCATION> Lynn </LOCATION>, a industrial city of 78,500 people about 15 miles north of <LOCATION> Boston </LOCATION>. During his trial last summer, the child talked about visits to <PERSON> Poole </PERSON>'s apartment on weekends but did not accuse him of any sexual misconduct. <PERSON> Stephen </PERSON> <PERSON> O'Connell </PERSON>, a spokesman for <ORGANIZATION> Essex </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> County </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> District </ORGANIZATION> Attorney <PERSON> Kevin </PERSON> <PERSON> Burke </PERSON>, said the girl had previously given investigators a detailed account of abuse but `` froze up'' on the witness stand. Following his acquittal, <PERSON> Poole </PERSON> was reinstated to the police department with back pay.
