<HEAD>School Board Makes Flag Salute Mandatory Despite State Policy</HEAD>
<DATELINE>YERMO, Calif. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 Students will be required to salute the flag under a school board decision directing district administrators to delete a section of the state education code stating that a salute is not mandatory. `` Communism comes from liberalism,'' <ORGANIZATION> Silver </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Valley </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Unified </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> School </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> District </ORGANIZATION> board president <PERSON> Bob </PERSON> <PERSON> Woltman </PERSON> said Wednesday, adding that he is `` tired of liberalism in public schools.'' `` It's good for kids to honor our flag, as it shows love for a country that offers the greatest opportunity in the world for people of all faiths and races,'' said Trustee <PERSON> Carl </PERSON> <PERSON> von </PERSON> <PERSON> Badinski </PERSON>. A part of the education code allowing school boards to conform with a federal court ruling on individual freedom states: `` Individuals shall not be required to participate in the salute to the flag.'' Trustees of the district in the middle of the <LOCATION> Mojave </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Desert </LOCATION> ordered administrators to delete the paragraph when the policy comes up for final board review on March 27. According to the district's assistant superintendent, <PERSON> William </PERSON> <PERSON> Maybee </PERSON>, other provisions of the education code require elementary school classes to begin each day with the <ORGANIZATION> Pledge </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> of </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Allegiance </ORGANIZATION> and `` an appropriate patriotic exercise'' in secondary school classes. The <ORGANIZATION> U.S. </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Supreme </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Court </ORGANIZATION> in 1943 ruled that the government may not compel citizens to salute the flag. `` Freedom of religion has nothing to do with saluting the flag,'' <PERSON> von </PERSON> <PERSON> Badinski </PERSON> said. `` In this country, people have the right to worship any religion they desire, but it does n't give them the right not to salute the flag.''
