<HEAD>Flight 103: Chronology of Warnings, Terrorist Threats</HEAD>
<HEAD>With AM-Flight 103 Bjt</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LONDON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 Here are some key dates in the chronology of warnings and terrorist threats surrounding the bombing of <ORGANIZATION> Pan </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Am </ORGANIZATION> Flight 103:
</TEXT>
<NOTE>1988</NOTE>
<TEXT>
 OCTOBER _ West German authorities conducting raids discover a radio-cassette player containing plastic explosives and a barometric timing device that could be set to detonate a bomb at a given altitude. Thirteen alleged members of the Syrian-backed <ORGANIZATION> Popular </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Front </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> for </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> the </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Liberation </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> of </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Palestine-General </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Command </ORGANIZATION> guerrilla group are arrested. NOV. 18 _ The date <ORGANIZATION> Trans </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> World </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Airlines </ORGANIZATION> says the <ORGANIZATION> Federal </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Aviation </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Administration </ORGANIZATION> told it of the bomb found in <LOCATION> West </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Germany </LOCATION>. NOV. 22 _ The <ORGANIZATION> British </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Department </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> of </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Transport </ORGANIZATION> issues a bulletin via telex to `` relevant security authorities'' reporting discovery of bomb in <LOCATION> West </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Germany </LOCATION>. It now says that warning would have been circulated by the <ORGANIZATION> Federal </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Aviation </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Authority </ORGANIZATION> to <LOCATION> U.S. </LOCATION> airlines and other agencies that would need to know. DEC. 5 _ The <ORGANIZATION> U.S. </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Embassy </ORGANIZATION> in <LOCATION> Helsinki </LOCATION> is warned in a telephone call of a plot to bomb a <ORGANIZATION> Pan </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Am </ORGANIZATION> airliner on a Frankfurt-U.S. flight during a two-week period in December. The <ORGANIZATION> Federal </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Aviation </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Administration </ORGANIZATION> issues an `` intell