<NOTE>1989</NOTE>
<TEXT>
 JAN. 17 _ The date <ORGANIZATION> Pan </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Am </ORGANIZATION> says it received a memo by mail from the <ORGANIZATION> British </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Department </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> of </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Transport </ORGANIZATION> dated Dec. 19. MAR. 15 _ The <ORGANIZATION> British </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Department </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> of </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Transport </ORGANIZATION> first announces it alerted airlines and airports on Dec. 19 about a possible terrorist attack with precise details similar to the device that destroyed Flight 103.
