<DATELINE>MANILA, Philippines (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 Communist rebels killed a police intelligence agent Wednesday in a <LOCATION> Manila </LOCATION> suburb, and the military said nine other people were slain in clashes between insurgents and government forces. Police said <PERSON> Patrolman </PERSON> <PERSON> Leandro </PERSON> <PERSON> Serrano </PERSON> was in his jeep preparing to leave for work in suburban Navotas when five gunmen opened fire, killing him instantly. The assailants, who escaped, left a note signed by the <ORGANIZATION> Alex </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Boncayao </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Brigade </ORGANIZATION> saying <PERSON> Serrano </PERSON> was slain because he was assigned to a police counterintelligence unit. The <PERSON> Alex </PERSON> <PERSON> Boncayao </PERSON> <PERSON> Brigade </PERSON> is the <LOCATION> Manila </LOCATION> wing of the <ORGANIZATION> New </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> People </ORGANIZATION><ORGANIZATION> 's </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Army </ORGANIZATION>, which has been waging a 20-year insurgency to establish a Communist state On <LOCATION> Mindanao </LOCATION> island, 500 miles southeast of <LOCATION> Manila </LOCATION>, the military said three rebels and three soldiers were killed Monday in <LOCATION> Lanao </LOCATION> <LOCATION> del </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Norte </LOCATION> province. Three more soldiers died in rebel ambushes the same day in the <LOCATION> Mindanao </LOCATION> provinces of <ORGANIZATION> Agusan </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> del </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Norte </ORGANIZATION> and <PERSON> Surigao </PERSON> <PERSON> del </PERSON> <PERSON> Norte </PERSON>, military reports said. In another development, the military said nine soldiers and four <ORGANIZATION> Defense </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Department </ORGANIZATION> civilians were fired for financial irregularities as part of a crackdown on corruption. Chief of Staff Gen. <PERSON> Renato </PERSON> <PERSON> de </PERSON> <PERSON> Villa </PERSON> said the 13 dismissed employees had finan