<FIRST>r f PM-Lampreys-Lakes     03-16 0320</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-Lampreys-Lakes,0330</SECOND>
<HEAD>Federal Help Needed to Stop Spread of Lampreys, Congressman Says</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By KIM I. MILLS</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>Associated Press Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 The Great Lakes region needs $ 9 million to buy the only known chemical to kill the sea lamprey and develop other means of controlling the parasitic eel or risk devastation of the salmon and trout population, a <LOCATION> New </LOCATION> <LOCATION> York </LOCATION> congressman says. Rep. <PERSON> Frank </PERSON> <PERSON> Horton </PERSON>, <LOCATION> R-N.Y. </LOCATION>, said Wednesday that without the expenditure, the lamprey population could double by the year 2000. If the lampreys double, `` this will cause the salmon and trout populations to be cut in half, costing sport and commercial fisheries an annual economic loss of $ 1.4 billion and some 33,600 jobs in the Great Lakes basin,'' He said the regional <ORGANIZATION> Great </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Lakes </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Fishery </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Commission </ORGANIZATION>, based in <LOCATION> Ann </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Arbor </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Mich. </LOCATION>, needs $ 9 million `` to keep the lamprey under control and the fishery thriving.'' Lampreys, native to the <LOCATION> Atlantic </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Ocean </LOCATION>, entered the Great Lakes through the Erie Canal in the 1880s and decimated the trout, whitefish and chub populations. They attach to fish with their sucking mouthpiece and feed on body fluids, sometimes killing the host. `` Anyone who has been around long enough can remember a time when it seemed every trout and salmon pulled from <LOCATION> Lake </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Ontario </LOCATION> had at least one, and sometimes more, lamprey eels stuck to their side,'' <PERSON> Horton </PERSON> said. `` The lamprey eel devastated the Great Lakes fishing industry a few years ago, but we've come back from it.'' The only safe and effective lamprey killer is a chemical, <ORGANIZATION> TFM </ORGANIZATION>, that is manufactured in <LOCATION> West </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Germany </LOCATION>, <PERSON> Horton </PERSON> said. But as the value of the dollar has dropped against the mark, the price of <ORGANIZATION> TFM </ORGANIZATION> has risen, he said. `` In an effort to find alternatives to the single-source chemical, we are requesting $ 1.3 million for the <LOCATION> U.S </LOCATION>. Fish and <ORGANIZATION> Wildlife </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Service </ORGANIZATION>'s efforts to develop a sterile male program to eradicate the lamprey population,'' he said.
