<HEAD>Jobless Rate Falls to 6.8 Percent, Lowest Level Since 1980</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LONDON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 Unemployment in <LOCATION> Britain </LOCATION> fell 0.2 percentage point to a seasonally adjusted 6.8 percent of the work force in February, its lowest level in more than eight years, the government said Thursday. The unemployment rate stood at 7 percent in January and at 8.7 percent in February 1988, according to the Department of Employment. The latest unemployment rate was the lowest since December, 1980, it said. The seasonally adjusted number of unemployed was 1.95 million in February, a revised 1.99 million in January, and 2.485 million in February 1988.
