<HEAD>Production Goes Down This Week</HEAD>
<DATELINE>DETROIT (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 Domestic automakers were scheduled to produce 245,152 cars and light trucks this week, down from last week's 247,128, <PERSON> Ward </PERSON>'s Automotive Reports said Thursday This week's production is higher than the same week a year ago, in which 230,813 cars and light trucks were produced, the trade journal said. <LOCATION> U.S. </LOCATION> automakers were scheduled to make 151,409 cars this week, compared with 156,692 a week ago and 147,039 in the same week in 1988. Light truck production for the week was scheduled at 93,743, compared with last week's 90,436 and last year's 83,774. Canadian automakers were to build 19,152 cars this week, down from 19,305 a week ago but up from last year's 18,884. Canadian light truck production was scheduled at 19,997, compared with 21,287 a week ago and 20,262 in the same week last year.
